{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GG7Fts233AYcjtD9q9gGYD","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# userservice\n2\t\n3\tPurpose: Composite package providing a complete in-process user CRUD service — an HTTP handler layer backed by a thread-safe in-memory store.\n4\tThe two sub-packages together form the full request-to-storage path for user records.\n5\t\n6\tTags: architecture, overview\n7\t\n8\t## Overview\n9\t\n10\t`userservice` contains the `handlers` and `store` sub-packages. Together they implement all user-management functionality: routing HTTP requests, performing in-memory data operations, and returning JSON responses. `main.go` at the project root wires these two packages into a running server on `:8080`.\n11\t\n12\t## Components\n13\t\n14\t| Sub-package | Responsibility | Doc |\n15\t|-------------|----------------|-----|\n16\t| [`handlers/`](handlers/README.md) | Routes `/users` HTTP requests to store operations and encodes JSON responses |\n17\t| [`store/`](store/README.md) | Thread-safe in-memory UUID-keyed CRUD store for `User` records |\n18\t\n19\t## Synthesis Docs\n20\t\n21\t- [data-flow.md](data-flow.md) — how an HTTP request travels from the mux through handlers into the store and back\n22\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7c568cc0-2dba-43d9-9faa-743c64f7ae41","uuid":"eb0d7931-2b93-47a0-b825-4fc1db6ef0a5","timestamp":"2026-04-05T22:45:25.852Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/establish-regression-recordings/sandbox/regressions/doc-user-service/output/internal/userservice/README.md","content":"# userservice\n\nPurpose: Composite package providing a complete in-process user CRUD service — an HTTP handler layer backed by a thread-safe in-memory store.\nThe two sub-packages together form the full request-to-storage path for user records.\n\nTags: architecture, overview\n\n## Overview\n\n`userservice` contains the `handlers` and `store` sub-packages. Together they implement all user-management functionality: routing HTTP requests, performing in-memory data operations, and returning JSON responses. `main.go` at the project root wires these two packages into a running server on `:8080`.\n\n## Components\n\n| Sub-package | Responsibility | Doc |\n|-------------|----------------|-----|\n| [`handlers/`](handlers/README.md) | Routes `/users` HTTP requests to store operations and encodes JSON responses |\n| [`store/`](store/README.md) | Thread-safe in-memory UUID-keyed CRUD store for `User` records |\n\n## Synthesis Docs\n\n- [data-flow.md](data-flow.md) — how an HTTP request travels from the mux through handlers into the store and back\n","numLines":22,"startLine":1,"totalLines":22}}}
